      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BROADWAY KING (8) hit the ground running and was prominent to the turn but faded out of it when 8th at The Gardens in Grade 5 company. The form out of his last race has been franked. Has ability and can bounce back. SPECIAL STYLE (1) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing seventh (23.03) last time in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Can measure up this time. CHA CHA ETHICS (3) has a moderate overall strike-rate. Finished second (25.42) at Goulburn latest and might be close to finding winning form again. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Leading chance. ZIPPING NEBULA (4) is a last-start placegetter here at this trip - worth considering.",
